        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 3:04PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Ricardo to 7 miles east of
Riviera Beach to 8 miles northeast of Kenedy County Wind Farms. These
storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Riviera Beach and Loyola Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
